{
  "id": "ramp-url-maze",
  "kind": "problem",
  "title": "API Maze Crawler",
  "difficulty": "hard",
  "concepts": [
    "API traversal",
    "graph traversal",
    "response parsing",
    "retries",
    "cycle detection"
  ],
  "prompt": "I give you a starting URL and a tiny HTTP-like helper. When you fetch a URL, the response may point you at more URLs. Somewhere in that maze there may be a response whose body is exactly `\"congrats\"`.\n\nWrite `find_final_url(start_url, max_retries)`.\n\nYour job is to crawl from `start_url` and return the URL whose response is `\"congrats\"`. Return `None`/`null` if you cannot reach one.\n\nIn a real interview this would probably be an HTTP client or a provided helper. In this app, the test harness provides the helper and backs it with hidden test data:\n\n- Python: call `fetch_url(url)`.\n- TypeScript: call `fetchUrl(url)`.\n- Go: call `FetchURL(url)`.\n- Scala: call `MazeApi.fetchUrl(url)`.\n\nEach call returns one response body. A body can be:\n\n- The string `\"congrats\"`: you found the answer; return the URL you just fetched.\n- An object/dict/map containing `\"urls\"`: those are the next URLs discovered from this page, in order.\n- An object/dict/map with `\"status\": 503`: a temporary failure for this URL.\n- Anything else: treat it as a dead end.\n\nSome URLs are flaky. If a fetch returns status `503`, retry that same URL immediately, up to `max_retries` extra times. For example, if a URL returns `503`, then `503`, then `\"congrats\"`, it is reachable when `max_retries` is `2`, but not when `max_retries` is `1`.\n\nThe maze can contain cycles and duplicate links. Do not get stuck repeatedly processing the same URL. If several successful URLs could lead to `\"congrats\"`, return the one reachable in the fewest number of link hops from `start_url`. If there is still a tie, use the order in which URLs are returned by the API.\n\nThe hidden service behaves like this: each URL has a response transcript. The first time you fetch it, you receive the first response; the second time, the second response; after the transcript runs out, the service keeps returning the last response.\n\nVisible example A:\n\n```python\n# hidden fake service\n{\n  \"http://start\": {\"urls\": [\"http://a\", \"http://b\"]},\n  \"http://a\": {\"message\": \"nothing here\"},\n  \"http://b\": \"congrats\"\n}\n\nfind_final_url(\"http://start\", 2) == \"http://b\"\n```\n\nVisible example B:\n\n```python\n# hidden fake service\n{\n  \"s\": {\"urls\": [\"r\"]},\n  \"r\": [{\"status\": 503}, {\"status\": 503}, \"congrats\"]\n}\n\nfind_final_url(\"s\", 2) == \"r\"\n```\n\nYou do not need real network access, sleeps, exponential backoff, threads, or async code. Focus on the crawling logic, retry boundary, response parsing, and cycle safety.",
  "signature": {
    "name": "findFinalUrl",
    "inputs": [
      {
        "name": "start_url",
        "type": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "max_retries",
        "type": {
          "type": "number"
        }
      }
    ],
    "output": {
      "type": "string",
      "nullable": true
    }
  },
  "tests": [
    {
      "name": "start already succeeds",
      "args": [
        "done",
        3
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "done": "congrats"
      },
      "expected": "done",
      "visibility": "visible"
    },
    {
      "name": "branch with one dead end",
      "args": [
        "http://start",
        2
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "http://start": {
          "urls": [
            "http://a",
            "http://b"
          ],
          "meta": 1
        },
        "http://a": {
          "message": "nothing here"
        },
        "http://b": "congrats"
      },
      "expected": "http://b",
      "visibility": "visible"
    },
    {
      "name": "retry succeeds",
      "args": [
        "s",
        2
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "s": {
          "urls": [
            "r"
          ]
        },
        "r": [
          {
            "status": 503
          },
          {
            "status": 503
          },
          "congrats"
        ]
      },
      "expected": "r",
      "visibility": "visible"
    },
    {
      "name": "cycle without success",
      "args": [
        "u1",
        1
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "u1": {
          "urls": [
            "u2"
          ]
        },
        "u2": {
          "urls": [
            "u1",
            "u3"
          ]
        },
        "u3": {
          "info": "dead end"
        }
      },
      "expected": null,
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
      "name": "closest success beats earlier deep branch",
      "args": [
        "start",
        1
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "start": {
          "urls": [
            "left",
            "right"
          ]
        },
        "left": {
          "urls": [
            "deep"
          ]
        },
        "right": "congrats",
        "deep": "congrats"
      },
      "expected": "right",
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
      "name": "tie follows API order",
      "args": [
        "start",
        1
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "start": {
          "urls": [
            "left",
            "right"
          ]
        },
        "left": {
          "urls": [
            "left-exit"
          ]
        },
        "right": {
          "urls": [
            "right-exit"
          ]
        },
        "left-exit": "congrats",
        "right-exit": "congrats"
      },
      "expected": "left-exit",
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
      "name": "too many retries skips flaky URL",
      "args": [
        "root",
        1
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "root": {
          "urls": [
            "slow",
            "fallback"
          ]
        },
        "slow": [
          {
            "status": 503
          },
          {
            "status": 503
          },
          "congrats"
        ],
        "fallback": "congrats"
      },
      "expected": "fallback",
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
      "name": "permanent 503 is not success",
      "args": [
        "root",
        3
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "root": {
          "urls": [
            "slow"
          ]
        },
        "slow": [
          {
            "status": 503
          }
        ]
      },
      "expected": null,
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
      "name": "missing URL is ignored",
      "args": [
        "start",
        2
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "start": {
          "urls": [
            "missing",
            "exit"
          ]
        },
        "exit": "congrats"
      },
      "expected": "exit",
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
      "name": "duplicate links do not repeat work",
      "args": [
        "start",
        2
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "start": {
          "urls": [
            "a",
            "a",
            "b"
          ]
        },
        "a": {
          "urls": [
            "start"
          ]
        },
        "b": "congrats"
      },
      "expected": "b",
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
      "name": "malformed list body is a dead end",
      "args": [
        "root",
        1
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "root": {
          "urls": [
            "bad",
            "good"
          ]
        },
        "bad": [
          [
            1,
            2,
            3
          ]
        ],
        "good": "congrats"
      },
      "expected": "good",
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
      "name": "urls must be a list",
      "args": [
        "root",
        1
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "root": {
          "urls": [
            "weird",
            "exit"
          ]
        },
        "weird": {
          "urls": "exit"
        },
        "exit": "congrats"
      },
      "expected": "exit",
      "visibility": "hidden"
    },
    {
      "name": "missing start",
      "args": [
        "missing",
        2
      ],
      "fixture": {
        "elsewhere": "congrats"
      },
      "expected": null,
      "visibility": "hidden"
    }
  ],
